FBIS4-34362 "drlat118_k_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-118 Daily Report 17 Jun 1994 SOUTH AMERICA Argentina Panama's Endara Agrees With Amnesty Bill Rejection Panama's Endara Agrees With Amnesty Bill Rejection PA1906191394 Panama City Telemetro Television Network in Spanish 1730 GMT 17 Jun 94 PA1906191394 Panama City Telemetro Television Network Spanish BFN [From the "Telemetro Reports" newscast] [Text] President Guillermo Endara continues his visit to Argentina. Last night Argentine President Carlos Menem hosted a dinner in his honor at the presidential palace. Today (Juan Bautista Joffre), former Argentine ambassador to Panama, will host a luncheon for the Panamanian president. This evening Endara will attend a tango musical performance in the traditional San Telmo neighborhood. Meanwhile, during statements to local media in Argentina, President Endara said that he agreed with the Legislative Assembly's rejection of the draft amnesty bill. Endara said that the manner in which this draft bill has been presented provided a wide loophole through which many criminals could escape.
